The paper discusses active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that focuses on selecting the most informative samples to label. The paper also mentions the use of estimators and approximations, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also presents fundamental active learning problems, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a tool for active learning, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SI).
